<name>VEHICLE STABILITY CONTROL SYSTEM (for BOSCH Made)</name>
<para id="RM000001NJJ001X" category="T" type-id="3001H" name-id="BC134-02" from="200601">
<name>PROBLEM SYMPTOMS TABLE</name>
<subpara id="RM000001NJJ001X_z0" proc-id="RM0250U___000012O00000">
<content5 releasenbr="1">
<ptxt>If there are no DTCs output but the problem still occurs, check the circuits for each problem symptom in the order given in the table below, and proceed to the relevant troubleshooting page.</ptxt>
<atten3>
<ptxt>Before replacing the brake actuator assembly, sensor, or other related parts, turn the ignition switch off.</ptxt>
</atten3>
<table frame="all" colsep="1" rowsep="1" pgwide="1">
<title>Vehicle stability control system:</title>
<tgroup cols="3" colsep="1" rowsep="1">
<colspec colnum="1" colname="1" colwidth="2.79in" colsep="0"/>
<colspec colnum="2" colname="2" colwidth="3.17in" colsep="0"/>
<colspec colnum="3" colname="3" colwidth="1.12in" colsep="0"/>
<thead valign="top">
<row rowsep="1">
<entry colname="1" colsep="1" align="center">
<ptxt>Symptom</ptxt>
</entry>
<entry colname="2" colsep="1" align="center">
<ptxt>Suspected area</ptxt>
</entry>
<entry colname="3" colsep="1" align="center">
<ptxt>See page</ptxt>
</entry>
</row>
</thead>
<tbody valign="top">
<row rowsep="1">
<entry colname="1" morerows="5" colsep="1" valign="middle" align="left">
<ptxt>ABS, BA and/or EBD does not operate</ptxt>
</entry>
<entry colname="2" colsep="1" align="left">
<ptxt>1. Check for the DTC again and make sure that the normal system code is output.</ptxt>
</entry>
<entry colname="3" colsep="1" align="left">
<ptxt>
<xref href="RM000001NK5001X" label="XX-XX"/>
</ptxt>
</entry>
</row>
<row rowsep="1">
<entry colname="2" colsep="1" align="left">
<ptxt>2. IG power source circuit</ptxt>
</entry>
<entry colname="3" colsep="1" align="left">
<ptxt>
<xref href="RM000001NJL001X" label="XX-XX"/>
</ptxt>
</entry>
</row>
<row rowsep="1">
<entry colname="2" colsep="1" align="left">
<ptxt>3. Front speed sensor circuit</ptxt>
</entry>
<entry colname="3" colsep="1" align="left">
<ptxt>
<xref href="RM000001NKF001X" label="XX-XX"/>
</ptxt>
</entry>
</row>
<row rowsep="1">
<entry colname="2" colsep="1" align="left">
<ptxt>4. Rear speed sensor circuit</ptxt>
</entry>
<entry colname="3" colsep="1" align="left">
<ptxt>
<xref href="RM000001NKG001X" label="XX-XX"/>
</ptxt>
</entry>
</row>
<row rowsep="1">
<entry colname="2" colsep="1" align="left">
<ptxt>5. Check the brake actuator assembly with the intelligent tester (Check brake actuator assembly operation using the active test function). If abnormal, check the hydraulic circuit for leakage.</ptxt>
</entry>
<entry colname="3" colsep="1" align="left">
<ptxt>
<xref href="RM0000013P9005X" label="XX-XX"/>
</ptxt>
</entry>
</row>
<row rowsep="1">
<entry colname="2" colsep="1" align="left">
<ptxt>6. If the symptoms still occur even after the above circuits in suspected areas have been inspected and proved to be normal, replace the brake actuator assembly (skid control ECU).</ptxt>
</entry>
<entry colname="3" colsep="1" align="left">
<ptxt>
<xref href="RM0000013P6004X" label="XX-XX"/>
</ptxt>
</entry>
</row>
<row rowsep="1">
<entry colname="1" morerows="5" colsep="1" valign="middle" align="left">
<ptxt>ABS, BA and/or EBD does not operate efficiently</ptxt>
</entry>
<entry colname="2" colsep="1" align="left">
<ptxt>1. Check for the DTC again and make sure that the normal system code is output.</ptxt>
</entry>
<entry colname="3" colsep="1" align="left">
<ptxt>
<xref href="RM000001NK5001X" label="XX-XX"/>
</ptxt>
</entry>
</row>
<row rowsep="1">
<entry colname="2" colsep="1" align="left">
<ptxt>2. Front speed sensor circuit</ptxt>
</entry>
<entry colname="3" colsep="1" align="left">
<ptxt>
<xref href="RM000001NKF001X" label="XX-XX"/>
</ptxt>
</entry>
</row>
<row rowsep="1">
<entry colname="2" colsep="1" align="left">
