</entry>
<entry colname="3" colsep="1" align="left">
<ptxt>
<xref href="RM000001NKG001X" label="XX-XX"/>
</ptxt>
</entry>
</row>
<row rowsep="1">
<entry colname="2" colsep="1" align="left">
<ptxt>4. Stop light switch circuit</ptxt>
</entry>
<entry colname="3" colsep="1" align="left">
<ptxt>
<xref href="RM0000025HM000X" label="XX-XX"/>
</ptxt>
</entry>
</row>
<row rowsep="1">
<entry colname="2" colsep="1" align="left">
<ptxt>5. Check the brake actuator assembly with the intelligent tester (Check brake actuator assembly operation using the active test function). If abnormal, check the hydraulic circuit for leakage.</ptxt>
</entry>
<entry colname="3" colsep="1" align="left">
<ptxt>
<xref href="RM0000013P9005X" label="XX-XX"/>
</ptxt>
</entry>
</row>
<row rowsep="1">
<entry colname="2" colsep="1" align="left">
<ptxt>6. If the symptoms still occur even after the above circuits in suspected areas have been inspected and proved to be normal, replace the brake actuator assembly (skid control ECU).</ptxt>
</entry>
<entry colname="3" colsep="1" align="left">
<ptxt>
<xref href="RM0000013P6004X" label="XX-XX"/>
</ptxt>
</entry>
</row>
<row rowsep="1">
<entry colname="1" morerows="7" colsep="1" valign="middle" align="left">
